doc.previous: Due to its long history the state of New York has several overlapping and often conflicting definitions of regions within the state This is further exacerbated by the colloquial use of such regional labels The New York State Department of Economic Development provides two distinct definitions of these regions It divides the state into ten economic regions 60 which approximately correspond to terminology used by residents
doc.after: The Department of Economic Development also groups the counties into eleven regions for tourism purposes 61
